    "body": "## Motivation\n\nIn mixed-precision scenarios (e.g., fp4/fp8 combined with fp32), the vectorization length of a vectorized loop is constrained by the GCD of all involved dtypes. For example:\n\n```python\nfor i in T.vectorized(16):\n    b[i] = b_frag[i]  # b: fp4, b_frag: fp32\n```\n\nSince the GCD of fp4 (4-bit) and fp32 (32-bit) is 4-bit, the entire loop can only be vectorized at 4-bit granularity, preventing efficient memory access with larger vector widths.\n\n## Solution\n\nIntroduce `DecoupleTypeCast` pass that inserts intermediate local buffers to decouple type conversion from memory access vectorization constraints.\n\n**Case 1: local → memory (store with mixed types)**\n\nBefore:\n```python\nfor i in T.vectorized(16):\n    b[i] = T.cast(b_frag[i], \"fp4\")  # constrained by GCD(fp4, fp32)\n```\n\nAfter:\n```python\nfor i in T.vectorized(16):\n    cast_buf[i] = T.cast(b_frag[i], \"fp4\")  # local→local, vectorize by fp32\nfor i in T.vectorized(16):\n    b[i] = cast_buf[i]                       # local→memory, vectorize by fp4\n```\n\n**Case 2: memory → local (load with different dtype)**\n\nBefore:\n```python\nfor i in T.vectorized(16):\n    a_frag[i] = T.cast(b[i], \"fp32\")  # constrained by GCD\n```\n\nAfter:\n```python\nfor i in T.vectorized(16):\n    cast_buf[i] = b[i]                       # memory→local, vectorize by fp4\nfor i in T.vectorized(16):\n    a_frag[i] = T.cast(cast_buf[i], \"fp32\")  # local→local, vectorize by fp32\n```\n\n## Changes\n\n- **New pass**: `tilelang/transform/decouple_type_cast.py` - implements IR transformation for both cases above\n- **C++ vectorize planner**: `src/transform/loop_vectorize.cc` - adjusts vectorization strategy to handle global/shared buffers separately from local buffers\n- **Pass config**: adds `TL_VECTORIZE_VERBOSE` for debugging\n- **Tests**: IR-level and CUDA codegen tests\n\n## Example Output\n\nIn generated CUDA code, fp4 memory copy can use `fp4_e2_16_t` (64-bit vectorized load/store), while type conversion loops are handled independently:\n\n```cpp\nfp4_e2_t b_local_cast[16];\n// type conversion loop\nfor (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {\n    fp4_e2_4_t __1;\n    float4 v_ = *(float4*)(b_frag + (i * 4));\n    (reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&__1))[0] = __tl_cvt_float2_to_fp4x2(...);\n    ...\n}\n// vectorized memory copy\n*(fp4_e2_16_t*)(b + 0) = *(fp4_e2_16_t*)(b_local_cast + 0);\n```\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added a vectorized iteration API (Vectorized alias).\n  * Introduced a DecoupleTypeCast transformation pass and exposed a toggle for verbose planner output.\n  * Exposed a target capability check for 256-bit vectorization and a small utility to detect local buffers.\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Corrected logical evaluation in target capability checks.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added tests covering the DecoupleTypeCast pass, including CUDA codegen paths.\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Simplified example scripts by removing redundant kernel parameters.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
